Burundian Tax Collection Increased by  35% in May, Revenue Authority Says

-- B y   D e s i r e   N i m u b o n a
-- 
2011-06-22T07:00:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/burundian-tax-collection-increased-by-35-in-may-revenue-authority-says.html
Revenue collection in Burundi rose
35 percent last month to 38.03 billion francs ($30.6 million),
the Burundi Revenue Authority said.  The increase brought total revenue collected in the first
five months of 2011 to 207.4 billion francs, up 42 percent from
the same period a year earlier, the Bujumbura-based authority
said in a statement on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Desire Nimubona in Bujumbura at 
 dnimubona@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  